				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\frac{1}{2}$$\end{document}12 0), resulting in a 2 × 2 CDW. Examples of multiple-q CDW orders have been observed in the AV3Sb542,43 (A = K, Rb) and ScV6Sn6
44 series of the kagome family. In the weakly correlated AV3Sb545,46, the first order phase transition is achieved without phonon softening47, pointing to a prominent role of order-disorder scenarios48,49. In contrast, the ground state of ScV6Sn6 displays a different lattice landscape, with the collapse of a high-temperature soft mode at q*=(\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
